# GTKwinInstaller — per-consumer configuration
#
# Submodule usage:
#   1. cp installer.env.example ../installer.env   (or wherever, outside the submodule)
#   2. Fill in the values below
#   3. make -C installer package-windows INSTALLER_ENV=../installer.env
#
# Standalone usage:
#   Edit config.rs and app/ directly instead — no env file needed.
#
# Any key left commented-out falls back to the default in config.rs.

# ─── Branding ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# APP_NAME=My App
# PUBLISHER=My Company
# APP_ID=com.mycompany.myapp

# ─── License page ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Path relative to the installer executable. Leave empty to disable.
# LICENSE_FILE=LICENSE

# ─── Installer behaviour ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Filename of the user's app executable in the install directory.
# Used for desktop/start-menu shortcuts and to launch the app after "Finish".
# Leave empty (or unset) to skip shortcuts and auto-launch.
# APP_EXE=myapp.exe

# Set to 1 to bundle setup.exe as the uninstaller (use when the target app is
# not a GTK app and won't have the GTK runtime in the install directory).
# BUNDLED_UNINSTALLER=0

# ─── App icon variant ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to 1 to bake the dark-variant icon (app-icon-dark.svg/png) into the exe.
# APP_ICON_DARK=1

# ─── Payload paths ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# APP_DIR: directory whose contents are copied to the install destination.
# APP_DIR=../dist

# ASSETS_DIR: installer branding assets (SVGs/PNGs for welcome/success/error).
# ASSETS_DIR=../branding/assets

# LICENSE: license file shown to the user during installation.
# LICENSE=../dist/LICENSE

# ─── Translations ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PO_DIR: directory containing .po files compiled into the installer.
# Built-in translations (po/*.po) are always included; PO_DIR files override
# per-language and can add new languages. Use this to customise installer
# strings or add a translation not in the built-in set.
# Run `make -C installer update-pot` to generate a .pot template to translate.
# PO_DIR=../myapp-translations

# ─── Optional app build hook ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Command run before staging (leave empty if app is pre-built).
# APP_BUILD=cargo build --release --manifest-path ../myapp/Cargo.toml
